org.hl7.cdsinput.r2

Class CDSContext

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.hl7.cdsinput.r2.CDSContext

  • public class CDSContext
extends Object
    The situation or context within which a CDS evaluation is made. Included in CDS inputs for HL7 Context-Aware Knowledge Retrieval (Infobutton) Knowledge Request standard. Used, for example, to generate human-readable care guidance in the end-user's preferred language.

    Java class for CDSContext complex type.

      • getTemplateId

        public List<CodedIdentifier> getTemplateId()
        Gets the value of the templateId property.

        This accessor method returns a reference to the live list, not a snapshot. Therefore any modification you make to the returned list will be present inside the JAXB object. This is why there is not a set method for the templateId property.

        For example, to add a new item, do as follows: 

            getTemplateId().add(newItem);

        Objects of the following type(s) are allowed in the list CodedIdentifier
